      "content": "Honesty is often the best policy, especially when maintaining client trust. If the new system is less nuanced, we should explicitly manage that expectation regarding highly complex requests. I propose we communicate that while the new AI excels at speed and standard queries, intricate, bespoke projects might require a brief manual handover to a human specialist for the time being. This keeps the door open for high-touch service while acknowledging the system's current limitations.",
